  "prompt": "How widely accepted are credit cards at small businesses and restaurants in Malta?",
  "response": "As of my latest update, credit cards are generally widely accepted at small businesses and restaurants in Malta, particularly in more tourist-centric areas and major towns. However, acceptance can vary depending on the establishment. Larger and more established businesses are more likely to accept credit cards, while smaller or family-run places might prefer cash due to transaction fees associated with card payments.\n\nIt's always a good idea to carry some cash just in case, especially if you plan to visit rural areas or smaller, local establishments. Additionally, many places in Malta have embraced contactless payment options, which include debit and credit cards, as well as mobile payment systems like Apple Pay and Google Pay.",
